                <head>177. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>French Foreign Minister <persName corresp="#p_PCP1">Christian Pineau</persName>
                    held a series of wide-ranging talks with United States officials on matters of
                    mutual concern to the United States and France during an official 3-day visit to
                    Washington, June 18–20. During these discussions, <persName corresp="#p_PCP1"
                        >Pineau</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_DAW1">Dulles</persName>
                    discussed the future of European integration efforts. Documentation on these
                    talks is scheduled for publication in a forthcoming <hi rend="italic">Foreign
                        Relations</hi> volume.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
